[SHORT DESC]
Cures poison. One-time use.

[LONG DESC]
<h2>Description</h2>
If held by a Pokemon, will automatically cure the poison or toxic poison status conditions when inflicted on the holder. Consumed after use. Can also be used forcibly by the trainer in-game. Natural Gift becomes a 60 Base Power Electric-type attack when the user holds this Berry, but the Berry is consumed after use.

<h2>Competitive Use</h2>
<p>This item is not seen in any tier because Lum Berry can cure any status ailment, while Pecha Berry can only cure one.</p>

<h2>Location</h2> 
<p>Pinwheel Forest - received from two different Pokemon Rangers.</p>
<p>Route 8 - received from two different Pokemon Rangers.</p>
<p>Studio Castelia in Castelia City - show Harlequin a Pokemon of the type he asks for.</p>
<p>Wild Venipede and Whirlipede (50%).</p>
<p>Wild Poochyena (5% - White only).</p>
<p>Dream World (Pleasant Forest).</p>